data.description: Welcome to 1423 Hazel Road! This charming brick ranch home has recently been updated and is located on a peaceful cul-de-sac street, which is close to shopping, dining, and major roadways, and just a few minutes away from MUSC and downtown Charleston! As you step inside, you'll be greeted by beautiful wood floors, fresh paint, smooth ceilings, French doors leading out to a brand-new deck, and large windows that provide plenty of natural light. The kitchen is spacious and comes equipped with ample cabinet and counter space, matching appliances, a gas stove, and a dining area. There are three generously sized bedrooms, one and a half baths, and a large laundry closet. The home sits on a lovely lot with a fenced backyard, blessing garden, and a convenient ramp leading to the side door.What's unique about this property?? For a qualified buyer there is a assumable VA loan of $225,000 at 2.25%.  This is a wonderful opportunity to own a lovely home in a desirable neighborhood. Flood Zone X, NO HOA bring your beach and water toys. The extended driveway allows for plenty of off-street parking. So, don't wait, schedule your showing today!
